headline: Kimberly-Clark’s (NASDAQ:KMB) Q4 CY2025 Earnings Results: Revenue In Line With Expectations
summary: Household products company Kimberly-Clark (NYSE:KMB) met Wall Streets revenue expectations in Q4 CY2025, but sales were flat year on year at $4.08 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $1.86 per share was 2.7% above analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: Kimberly-Clark Declares Dividend Increase
summary: The board of directors of Kimberly-Clark Corporation (NASDAQ: KMB) has declared an increase in its regular quarterly dividend to $1.28 per share, up from $1.26 previously. The dividend is payable in cash on April 2, 2026, to stockholders of record at the close of business on March 6, 2026.

headline: Kimberly-Clark Reports Strong Finish to Second Year of Transformation
summary: Kimberly-Clark Corporation (Nasdaq: KMB) today reported fourth quarter and full year 2025 results that reflect the momentum of its innovation-driven, volume-plus-mix led growth model. These are supported by significant efficiencies that are enabling strong reinvestment in its brands and capabilities, and generating attractive returns to its shareholders.
